## SVG Filter Breakdown

### 1. Turbulence Noise
```svg
<feTurbulence
    type="fractalNoise"
    baseFrequency="0.001 0.005"
    numOctaves="1"
    seed="17"
    result="turbulence"
/>
```
- Creates organic, natural-looking distortion patterns
- `baseFrequency` controls the scale of the noise
- `seed` determines the random pattern (17, 5, 14 are good seeds)

### 2. Gamma Correction
```svg
<feComponentTransfer in="turbulence" result="mapped">
    <feFuncR type="gamma" amplitude="1" exponent="10" offset="0.5" />
    <feFuncG type="gamma" amplitude="0" exponent="1" offset="0" />
    <feFuncB type="gamma" amplitude="0" exponent="1" offset="0.5" />
</feComponentTransfer>
```
- Adjusts color mapping for realistic distortion
- Creates contrast between light and dark areas

### 3. Gaussian Blur
```svg
<feGaussianBlur in="turbulence" stdDeviation="3" result="softMap" />
```
- Softens edges for natural glass appearance
- `stdDeviation="3"` controls blur intensity

### 4. Specular Lighting
```svg
<feSpecularLighting
    in="softMap"
    surfaceScale="5"
    specularConstant="1"
    specularExponent="100"
    lighting-color="white"
    result="specLight"
>
    <fePointLight x="-200" y="-200" z="300" />
</feSpecularLighting>
```
- Simulates realistic lighting on glass surface
- Creates highlights and reflections
- `specularExponent="100"` controls highlight sharpness

### 5. Displacement Mapping
```svg
<feDisplacementMap
    in="SourceGraphic"
    in2="softMap"
    scale="200"
    xChannelSelector="R"
    yChannelSelector="G"
/>
```
- Creates glass refraction effect
- `scale="200"` controls distortion intensity

